Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.01,0:02:00.28,Regular,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.28,0:02:01.72,Regular,,0,0,0,,What are you doing in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.72,0:02:02.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.46,0:02:04.77,Regular,,0,0,0,,How did you get in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.13,0:02:11.57,Regular,,0,0,0,,A Simoun really is totally\Ndifferent from a Simile, isn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.57,0:02:13.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,I asked you who you were.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.26,0:02:14.48,Regular,,0,0,0,,And that uniform…?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.23,0:02:17.04,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Wapourif.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.04,0:02:18.79,Regular,,0,0,0,,She’s our new recruit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.45,0:02:20.78,Regular,,0,0,0,,I beg your pardon!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.78,0:02:22.65,Regular,,0,0,0,,I didn’t realize you\Nwere a Simoun sibylla.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.65,0:02:25.21,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’m sorry. It was my fault as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.28,0:02:28.46,Regular,,0,0,0,,This is Morinas.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.46,0:02:29.47,Regular,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.16,0:02:38.52,Regular,,0,0,0,,Helical motors are always found in spiral-shaped pairs like these.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.70,0:02:46.59,Regular,,0,0,0,,We attach cockpits and various other equipment to control them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.59,0:02:50.98,Regular,,0,0,0,,We call the whole a Simoun\Nfor the sake of convenience.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.63,0:02:52.98,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yes, that’s right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.89,0:02:58.24,Regular,,0,0,0,,We think that this one\Nprobably manipulates—
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.24,0:02:59.74,Regular,,0,0,0,,“Probably?”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.74,0:03:03.24,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yes. We think this one manipulates
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.24,0:03:07.91,Regular,,0,0,0,,what you might call a spatial force, which exists throughout the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.91,0:03:13.49,Regular,,0,0,0,,The other one controls what we would describe as a temporal force.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.49,0:03:16.03,Regular,,0,0,0,,Is that also “probably?”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.03,0:03:17.76,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yes. Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.76,0:03:24.69,Regular,,0,0,0,,In fact, we know almost nothing about the helical motors we’ve excavated.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.69,0:03:25.80,Regular,,0,0,0,,All we know is…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.80,0:03:28.04,Regular,,0,0,0,,…how to use them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.04,0:03:33.94,Regular,,0,0,0,,Also, we can only maintain the parts that we’ve added to the helical motors.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.94,0:03:35.02,Regular,,0,0,0,,That’s the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.84,0:03:37.22,Regular,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.22,0:03:42.74,Regular,,0,0,0,,But the Simile were built to investigate the structure of the helical motors, weren’t they?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.74,0:03:48.84,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yes. But you’ve flown Simile up until now, so you must know how they perform.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.84,0:03:53.25,Regular,,0,0,0,,Compared to this Simoun, a Simile is nothing but a pale imitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.25,0:03:55.71,Regular,,0,0,0,,They don’t deserve to be\Nmentioned in the same breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.71,0:04:01.17,Regular,,0,0,0,,Well, I’ve heard that nobody’s ever taken apart a Simoun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.17,0:04:03.01,Regular,,0,0,0,,That seems rather strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.01,0:04:04.90,Regular,,0,0,0,,Strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.90,0:04:11.07,Regular,,0,0,0,,The Simoun are sacred craft built to serve Tempus Spatium in holy rituals.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.07,0:04:13.59,Regular,,0,0,0,,They must be treated\Nwith the proper respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.59,0:04:15.02,Regular,,0,0,0,,He’s right, Morinas.{** he?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.02,0:04:19.94,Regular,,0,0,0,,We are here to offer\NRi Maajons to Tempus Spatium.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.94,0:04:22.03,Regular,,0,0,0,,We are priestesses\Nserving Tempus Spatium.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.81,0:04:24.74,Regular,,0,0,0,,Well, I’m not really a priestess.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.74,0:04:27.07,Regular,,0,0,0,,Then what are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.07,0:04:29.88,Regular,,0,0,0,,I just want to fly a Simoun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.88,0:04:32.54,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’m not a priestess. But…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.54,0:04:33.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,But what?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.61,0:04:39.15,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’m not a soldier, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.15,0:04:41.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,Don’t you feel the same way, Paraietta?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.00,0:04:46.65,Regular,,0,0,0,,Oh, Paraietta. This is…?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.65,0:04:47.96,Regular,,0,0,0,,Her name is Morinas, Floe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.96,0:04:50.94,Regular,,0,0,0,,Oh, that’s right! You’re Morinas.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.84,0:04:53.64,Regular,,0,0,0,,Mo-ri-nas.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.64,0:04:55.09,Regular,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Floe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.09,0:04:58.11,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’m bad at remembering people’s names.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.11,0:04:59.15,Regular,,0,0,0,,And…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.77,0:05:07.03,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sorry, when I first saw you I thought for a second\Nthat you might be Wapourif’s new lover.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.06,0:05:10.03,Regular,,0,0,0,,But there’s just no way, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.49,0:05:15.74,Regular,,0,0,0,,My windshield is creaking.\NCan you take a look at it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.74,0:05:17.00,Regular,,0,0,0,,Certainly!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.70,0:05:19.69,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’d appreciate it if\Nyou could tell her more
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.69,0:05:22.83,Regular,,0,0,0,,about the differences between the Simile and the Simoun this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.83,0:05:24.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,That won’t be a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.40,0:05:30.05,Regular,,0,0,0,,If there’s anything you’d like to know about the Simoun,\Nor about this ship, come and ask us any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.05,0:05:31.64,Regular,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.80,0:05:38.90,Regular,,0,0,0,,Wait up! I’m coming too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.90,0:05:41.82,Regular,,0,0,0,,So, did you learn much, Morinas?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.82,0:05:45.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,Hopefully this afternoon I’ll be able to learn something interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.91,0:05:53.91,Titles,,90,0,0,,{\blur0.6}Distant War
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.21,0:07:41.39,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.39,0:07:44.58,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’m glad that you came\Nback from the Spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.34,0:07:51.35,Regular,,0,0,0,,May I take it that you have chosen to remain a Simoun sibylla?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.35,0:07:54.66,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’m not sure yet. And…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.66,0:07:56.12,Regular,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.06,0:07:59.96,Regular,,0,0,0,,I don’t have a pair any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.96,0:08:02.62,Regular,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless, you have returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.87,0:08:11.59,Regular,,0,0,0,,Huh? What’s going on, guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.59,0:08:13.59,Regular,,0,0,0,,You’re late, Aaeru.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.59,0:08:16.30,Regular,,0,0,0,,Oh, right! Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.13,0:08:19.64,Regular,,0,0,0,,Um, what’re we doing here again?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.64,0:08:23.56,Regular,,0,0,0,,We always gather in the\Nballroom after breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.56,0:08:27.56,Regular,,0,0,0,,I see. It’s a habit you picked up when you were flying the night shift, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.56,0:08:33.67,Regular,,0,0,0,,As I was saying, why don’t we all get together to do Maaju in the pool this afternoon at three?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.77,0:08:37.30,Regular,,0,0,0,,You mean all of us?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.30,0:08:39.08,Regular,,0,0,0,,Is this mandatory?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.48,0:08:42.44,Regular,,0,0,0,,So, at three o’clock, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.44,0:08:44.32,Regular,,0,0,0,,That sounds great!\NLet’s go in the pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.32,0:08:46.88,Regular,,0,0,0,,Especially since we’re now so— oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.41,0:08:51.97,Regular,,0,0,0,,We have lost three of our comrades.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.97,0:08:55.34,Regular,,0,0,0,,After that, three more\Nleft to go to the Spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.34,0:08:58.94,Regular,,0,0,0,,During this crisis, we have been relieved from night duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.79,0:09:01.35,Regular,,0,0,0,,We were the elite.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.35,0:09:07.07,Regular,,0,0,0,,We will regain our honour\Nas priestesses and as sibyllae.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.80,0:09:09.32,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’m looking forward to this!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.32,0:09:10.79,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’ve just joined,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.79,0:09:14.13,Regular,,0,0,0,,so it’ll be wonderful\Nto do Maaju with a real choir.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.13,0:09:17.37,Regular,,0,0,0,,And you want to do this\Nat three o’clock, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.37,0:09:20.12,Regular,,0,0,0,,Why is three o’clock\Nsuch a big deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.12,0:09:21.88,Regular,,0,0,0,,That’s when…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.09,0:09:34.89,Regular,,0,0,0,,Three o’clock is when Neviril\Nalways practices her Maaju.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.34,0:09:41.56,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sibylla Aurea Neviril!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.56,0:09:43.57,Regular,,0,0,0,,I am honoured to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.31,0:09:45.37,Regular,,0,0,0,,And you are…?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.37,0:09:50.27,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’ve just been ordered to join the greatest choir of all, Chor Tempest.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.27,0:09:51.32,Regular,,0,0,0,,Her name is Morinas.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.65,0:09:57.42,Regular,,0,0,0,,I see. I hope that you will get along well with the rest of the choir.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.66,0:10:05.75,Regular,,0,0,0,,Aaeru, please look after Morinas.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.75,0:10:09.75,Regular,,0,0,0,,Huh? But I thought\N{\i1}you{\i0} were my pair, Neviril?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.75,0:10:13.49,Regular,,0,0,0,,Don’t be so presumptuous! You’ve only flown together once.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.49,0:10:17.05,Regular,,0,0,0,,Don’t imagine that you\Ncan possibly replace Amuria.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.05,0:10:20.11,Regular,,0,0,0,,That’s enough, Paraietta.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.11,0:10:21.55,Regular,,0,0,0,,Umm…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.55,0:10:25.27,Regular,,0,0,0,,We’re meeting at the pool to do Maaju at three this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.27,0:10:26.58,Regular,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.58,0:10:30.68,Regular,,0,0,0,,That’s when you do\Nyour Maaju, isn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.68,0:10:34.49,Regular,,0,0,0,,If you haven’t chosen your\Npair yet, please consider me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.72,0:10:42.30,Regular,,0,0,0,,Morinas, your pair will come to you naturally during the course of a Maaju.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.30,0:10:44.53,Regular,,0,0,0,,It’s not something you can\Nsimply decide beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.53,0:10:48.54,Regular,,0,0,0,,I would be honoured to pair\Nwith you, Sibylla Aurea.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.46,0:10:50.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.53,0:11:27.04,Regular,,0,0,0,,Don’t be afraid. An attack like that could not possibly harm the {\i1}Arcus Prima{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.04,0:11:28.99,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yes, ma’am!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.99,0:11:35.21,Regular,,0,0,0,,If you want to become Simoun sibyllae, you should walk proudly, without fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.21,0:11:36.25,Regular,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.17,0:11:47.23,Regular,,0,0,0,,There seem to be quite\Na lot of those today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.09,0:11:50.56,Regular,,0,0,0,,Should we go out\Nand intercept them?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.56,0:11:52.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yeah, let’s go!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.40,0:11:55.28,Regular,,0,0,0,,We’re not allowed to fly\Ncombat duty at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.79,0:12:30.47,Regular,,0,0,0,,Their greetings seem\Na little too enthusiastic today.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.47,0:12:36.76,Regular,,0,0,0,,Their long-range shelling is mostly just irritating, but we can’t be certain they won’t get lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.76,0:12:39.98,Regular,,0,0,0,,I believe we may have to consider doing something about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.14,0:12:43.37,Regular,,0,0,0,,Is Chor Tempest still off line?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.99,0:12:47.34,Regular,,0,0,0,,They can handle being\Nwithout a few members.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.85,0:12:49.21,Regular,,0,0,0,,But not Neviril?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.21,0:12:54.28,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yes. No matter what we do,\Nif she doesn’t come back,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.28,0:12:57.00,Regular,,0,0,0,,Chor Tempest will remain in disarray.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.59,0:13:14.30,Regular,,0,0,0,,You’re here early, Aaeru.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.30,0:13:16.02,Regular,,0,0,0,,You too, Alti.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.68,0:13:19.15,Regular,,0,0,0,,We’ve still got more than\Nhalf an hour before three.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.15,0:13:25.20,Regular,,0,0,0,,You’re already here then, Nee-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.40,0:13:30.88,Regular,,0,0,0,,I went to your room to look for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.86,0:13:35.61,Regular,,0,0,0,,Since you’re sisters, how come the two of you don’t fly a Simoun together?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.61,0:13:40.35,Regular,,0,0,0,,Just because we’re sisters, it doesn’t mean we can fly together as auriga and sagitta.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.88,0:13:41.92,Regular,,0,0,0,,Have you tried it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.05,0:13:44.42,Regular,,0,0,0,,We don’t need to try it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.04,0:13:47.93,Regular,,0,0,0,,I guess I asked something \NI shouldn’t have.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.67,0:14:01.94,Regular,,0,0,0,,This ship must have been beautiful when it was\N a private liner used for viewing Ri Maajons.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.85,0:14:07.45,Regular,,0,0,0,,But now it’s been converted into a carrier for the Simoun choirs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.15,0:14:14.58,Regular,,0,0,0,,There are no more ladies and gentlemen coming and going, bathed in the fading evening light.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.58,0:14:19.96,Regular,,0,0,0,,We’re the only ones left standing in the square in front of the Grand Ballroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.96,0:14:21.60,Regular,,0,0,0,,Just the three of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.53,0:14:25.96,Regular,,0,0,0,,But I…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.04,0:14:29.47,Regular,,0,0,0,,I wouldn’t have it any other way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.48,0:14:40.73,Regular,,0,0,0,,That looks like so much fun.\NI can’t wait any longer!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.22,0:14:43.44,Regular,,0,0,0,,Can I fly this right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.44,0:14:46.87,Regular,,0,0,0,,The Simoun are different from the Simile.\NYou can’t fly one on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.87,0:14:50.16,Regular,,0,0,0,,You need a second person: your pair.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.16,0:14:51.49,Regular,,0,0,0,,Oh! Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.49,0:14:58.72,Regular,,0,0,0,,The helical motors are powered by Tempus Spatium’s grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.72,0:15:04.43,Regular,,0,0,0,,If either the auriga or the sagitta is absent, the Simoun won’t receive that blessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.03,0:15:07.91,Regular,,0,0,0,,It definitely requires a complete pair.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.91,0:15:10.84,Regular,,0,0,0,,Well, can I ask you something?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.84,0:15:11.97,Regular,,0,0,0,,Of course. What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.38,0:15:15.97,Regular,,0,0,0,,When did you go to the Spring?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.97,0:15:19.52,Regular,,0,0,0,,Two years and four months ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.52,0:15:21.69,Regular,,0,0,0,,When I met Floe this morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.69,0:15:24.32,Regular,,0,0,0,,it felt like there was something strange between you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.32,0:15:28.52,Regular,,0,0,0,,Actually, Floe and I used to be lovers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.52,0:15:30.49,Regular,,0,0,0,,L-Lovers?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.49,0:15:35.83,Regular,,0,0,0,,It was out of line for me to behave that way towards one of our honoured sibyllae, wasn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.83,0:15:38.16,Regular,,0,0,0,,No, I didn’t mean that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.15,0:15:42.92,Regular,,0,0,0,,But things are a little\Nawkward between us now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.46,0:15:54.76,Regular,,0,0,0,,You’re coming to the pool, aren’t you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.42,0:15:58.43,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’ve told you already.\NI won’t be doing Maaju.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.14,0:16:01.05,Regular,,0,0,0,,I have no desire\Nto choose another pair.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.05,0:16:02.16,Regular,,0,0,0,,That’s—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.67,0:16:03.69,Regular,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.30,0:16:06.21,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’m sorry for what\Nhappened to Amuria.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.21,0:16:09.54,Regular,,0,0,0,,Amuria was one of our dearest friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.14,0:16:14.92,Regular,,0,0,0,,So I think I understand how the people who went to the Spring after that must have felt.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.42,0:16:30.67,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril! We’re going to be much stronger!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.33,0:16:34.63,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril, don’t look! If you see their eyes,\N you won’t be able to kill them!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.53,0:17:42.38,Regular,,0,0,0,,Listen up, Morinas!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.38,0:17:44.91,Regular,,0,0,0,,You can choose anyone\Nto be your pair in the pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.91,0:17:47.54,Regular,,0,0,0,,You don’t need to worry about the pair you fly into battle with.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.54,0:17:52.05,Regular,,0,0,0,,So basically it’s first come, first served! You can pick the one you like and— ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.33,0:18:00.05,Regular,,0,0,0,,If we’re here, Neviril might not come.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.06,0:18:05.79,Regular,,0,0,0,,It’s pretty pointless to have\NMaaju practice without her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.79,0:18:07.06,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’m sure…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.09,0:18:10.56,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’m sure Neviril will come.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.56,0:18:14.78,Regular,,0,0,0,,It’ll be too bad for you\Nif she doesn’t, Paraietta— ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.90,0:18:23.92,Regular,,0,0,0,,As I thought, it doesn’t\Nlook like Neviril is coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.92,0:18:26.04,Regular,,0,0,0,,Should I go and get her?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.04,0:18:28.64,Regular,,0,0,0,,You can try, but it won’t do any good.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.41,0:18:33.42,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril went to the Spring,\Nbut she came back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.92,0:18:40.77,Regular,,0,0,0,,That means that she’s chosen to remain a Simoun sibylla of her own free will, doesn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.77,0:18:42.68,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yes, it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.68,0:18:44.72,Regular,,0,0,0,,Then, do you think she’ll come?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.81,0:19:37.00,Regular,,0,0,0,,What are you doing, Floe?\NWatch where you’re going!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.55,0:20:16.52,Regular,,0,0,0,,There’s no way we can do Maaju with everybody feeling like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.37,0:20:20.61,Regular,,0,0,0,,Can this really be Chor Tempest?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.48,0:20:27.13,Regular,,0,0,0,,You think so?\NMaybe you spoke too soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.71,0:20:42.76,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.80,0:21:02.28,Regular,,0,0,0,,Are you… in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.20,0:21:10.34,Regular,,0,0,0,,Are you…?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.79,0:22:18.03,Regular,,0,0,0,,No matter how you try to protect those girls, this is reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.48,0:22:26.77,Regular,,0,0,0,,Hang on! Hang on, I’ll get you out!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.77,0:22:27.99,Regular,,0,0,0,,Firefighting team, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.96,0:24:06.59,Titles,,85,0,0,,{\blur0.6}Next Episode
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.09,0:24:11.34,Regular,,0,0,0,,Limone, don’t be\Nsuch a slowpoke! Let’s go!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.93,0:24:15.47,Regular,,0,0,0,,Next time, on Simoun:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.18,0:24:17.72,Regular,,0,0,0,,Nearby War.
